 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Visualizing the Titanic Disaster\n",
    "\n",
    "Click the button below to run this notebook directly on Google Colab:\n",
    "\n",
    "[<img src=\"https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg\" align=\"left\">](https://colab.research.google.com/github)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Introduction:\n",
    "\n",
    "This exercise is based on the titanic Disaster dataset avaiable at [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic).  \n",
    "To know more about the variables check [here](https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic/data)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### Step 1. Import the necessary libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 2. Import the dataset from this [address](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thieu1995/csv-files/main/data/pandas/titanic.csv)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 3. Assign it to a variable to titanic"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thieu1995/csv-files/main/data/pandas/titanic.csv'\n",
    "titanic = pd.read_csv(url)\n",
    "titanic.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 4. Create a pie chart presenting the male/female proportion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "males = (titanic['Sex'] == 'male').sum()\n",
    "females = (titanic['Sex'] == 'female').sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "proportions = [males, females]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.pie(\n",
    "    proportions,\n",
    "    labels = ['Males', 'Females'],\n",
    "    shadow = False,\n",
    "    colors = ['blue','red'],\n",
    "    explode = (0.15 , 0),\n",
    "    startangle = 90,\n",
    "    autopct = '%1.1f%%'\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.axis('equal')\n",
    "plt.title(\"Sex Proportion\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 5. Create a scatterplot with the Fare payed and the Age, differ the plot color by gender"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lm = sns.lmplot(x = 'Age', y = 'Fare', data = titanic, hue = 'Sex', fit_reg=False)\n",
    "lm.set(title = 'Fare x Age')\n",
    "axes = lm.axes\n",
    "axes[0,0].set_ylim(-10,)\n",
    "axes[0,0].set_xlim(-5,85)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 6. How many people survived?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "titanic['Survived'].sum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 7. Create a histogram with the Fare payed"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = titanic.Fare.sort_values(ascending = False)\n",
    "binsVal = np.arange(0,600,10)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.hist(df, bins = binsVal)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Fare')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "plt.title('Fare Payed Histogram')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### BONUS: Create your own question and answer it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Question: Create a countplot to show the number of survivors based on passenger class (Pclass)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false\n   },
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
     "sns.countplot(x='Pclass', hue='Survived', data=titanic)\n",
     "plt.title('Survivors by Passenger Class')\n",
     "plt.xlabel('Class')\n",
     "plt.ylabel('Count')\n",
     "plt.show()"
    ]
  }
 ],
